GENERAL FORMULA ANALYSIS
================================================================================

For Paley tournament T_p with p prime, p ≡ 1 or 3 (mod 4):

  c_m(T_p) = (1/m) · [((p-1)/2)^m - (p-1)/2^m · S_m(p)]

where S_m(p) = Σ_{s=0}^{(m-1)/2} C(m, 2s) · (ε·p)^s

and ε = χ(-1) = (-1)^{(p-1)/2} = { +1 if p ≡ 1 (mod 4)
                                    { -1 if p ≡ 3 (mod 4)


--- m = 3 ---
  S_3(p) = 1 + 3·(εp)^1
  When p ≡ 1 (mod 4) (ε=+1):
    S_3 = 3p + 1
    Verify p=13: S=40, c_3=52 = 52
  When p ≡ 3 (mod 4) (ε=-1):
    S_3 = -3p + 1
    Verify p=7: S=-20, c_3=14 = 14

