GENERATING FUNCTION: det(I - xA) for Paley tournaments
================================================================================

THEOREM: For Paley tournament T_p:

  det(I - xA) = (1 - x·(p-1)/2) · [1 + x + x²·(1 - εp)/4]^{(p-1)/2}

where ε = χ(-1) = (-1)^{(p-1)/2}.

  - If p ≡ 1 (mod 4): ε=1,  quadratic = 1 + x + x²(1-p)/4
  - If p ≡ 3 (mod 4): ε=-1, quadratic = 1 + x + x²(1+p)/4

This gives: -log det(I - xA) = Σ_{m≥1} c_m x^m

Note: (1-xα)(1-xβ) = 1 + x + x²αβ where αβ = (1 - εp)/4.

  p=7 (ε=-1):
    αβ = (1 - εp)/4 = 2
    det(I-xA) = (1 - 3x) · (1 + x + 2x²)^3
    Verify at x=0.1: direct=0.9834496000, formula=0.9834496000, match=True
  p=11 (ε=-1):
    αβ = (1 - εp)/4 = 3
    det(I-xA) = (1 - 5x) · (1 + x + 3x²)^5
    Verify at x=0.1: direct=0.9212175897, formula=0.9212175897, match=True
  p=13 (ε=+1):
    αβ = (1 - εp)/4 = -3
    det(I-xA) = (1 - 6x) · (1 + x + -3x²)^6
    Verify at x=0.1: direct=0.6002921407, formula=0.6002921407, match=True
  p=19 (ε=-1):
    αβ = (1 - εp)/4 = 5
    det(I-xA) = (1 - 9x) · (1 + x + 5x²)^9
    Verify at x=0.1: direct=0.3517876292, formula=0.3517876292, match=True
  p=23 (ε=-1):
    αβ = (1 - εp)/4 = 6
    det(I-xA) = (1 - 11x) · (1 + x + 6x²)^11
    Verify at x=0.1: direct=-0.5117264691, formula=-0.5117264691, match=True
